<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1849-08-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1849-08-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="244" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d244">
                            <head><seg type="margin">[695]</seg> *<hi rend="italic">Commandant
                                        <persName type="from">Newton</persName>, United States Navy,
                                    to Lieutenant-Commandant <persName type="to">Totten</persName>,
                                    United States Navy.</hi></head>
                            <dateline><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Commandant’s
                                        Office</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Navy-Yard,
                                    Pensacola</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1849-08-20"><hi rend="italic">August</hi> 20,
                                1849</date>.</dateline>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: You will proceed to sea at once with
                                the steamer Water Witch, under your command; and you are hereby
                                strictly enjoined not to open the accompanying <hi rend="italic">sealed parcel</hi> until after your vessel crosses the bar and
                                the pilot leaves you.</p>
                            <p>I am, very respectfully, &amp;c.,</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <list>
                                        <item>JOHN THOMAS NEWTON,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Commandant.</hi></item>
                                        <item>Lieutenant-Commandant <hi rend="smallcaps">Geo. M.
                                                Totten</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Commanding United
                                                States Steamer Water Witch.</hi></item>
                                    </list>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>